The prime factorization of 342 is \(2\cdot 3\cdot 3\cdot 19\).
The prime factorization of 285 is \(3\cdot 3\cdot 5\cdot 19\).
The largest common factor of 342 and 285 is \(3\cdot 3\cdot 19 = 171\).
Final Answer: \boxed{$171$}. I hope it is correct.
